7 Qualitative Evaluation.content:
To study how well our model is able to produce segmentation masks based on the prompt, we use our model to perform prompt-based instance segmentation including point-based and box-based prompt prompt segmentation. We also take our model to perform segment everything and salient instance segmentation without manually creating point and box prompt.

For each task, we share 4 examples for showing the instance segmentation capabilities of our model. These results provide direct evidence for the competing instance segmentation capabilities of our EfficientSAM with different prompts. For example, in the case of point-prompt instance segmentation, our model is able to give reasonable instance segmentation results (see [Fig.8]In 7 Qualitative Evaluation ‚Ä£ EfficientSAM: Leveraged Masked Image Pretraining for Efficient Segment Anything")). In the case of box-prompt instance segmentation, our model also generates expected object segmentation (see [Fig.9]In 7 Qualitative Evaluation ‚Ä£ EfficientSAM: Leveraged Masked Image Pretraining for Efficient Segment Anything")). In the case of segment everything, our model provides decent segmentation performance (see [Fig.10]In 7 Qualitative Evaluation ‚Ä£ EfficientSAM: Leveraged Masked Image Pretraining for Efficient Segment Anything")). In the case of salient instance segmentation, our model has the ability of generating mask and gives automatic instance segmentation without manually creating points or boxes (see [Fig.11]In 7 Qualitative Evaluation ‚Ä£ EfficientSAM: Leveraged Masked Image Pretraining for Efficient Segment Anything")). But we still need to note that our model may sometimes produce noisy segmentation, shown in [Fig.12]In 7 Qualitative Evaluation ‚Ä£ EfficientSAM: Leveraged Masked Image Pretraining for Efficient Segment Anything").

